# Use Monorepo Workspace Imports

Always use full monorepo workspace paths for imports instead of relative paths or aliases.

## Format
Use the pattern: `@zenflux/<project-name>/path/to/file`

## Examples

✅ Correct:
```typescript
import { Button } from "@zenflux/app-budget-allocation/src/components/ui/button";
import { API } from "@zenflux/react-api/src";
import { useCommanderCommand } from "@zenflux/react-commander/use-commands";
```

❌ Incorrect:
```typescript
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Button } from "./button";
import { Button } from "../components/button";
```

## Why
- Ensures consistency across the monorepo
- Makes dependencies explicit and clear
- Avoids confusion with relative paths
- Works better with monorepo tooling